box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 0; text-align: left;
display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; color: #000000; line-height: 1.2; pointer-events: all; white-space: normal; word-wrap: normal;
div.div: 1a: FinTech calls OpenBankingGateway (OBG) to list accounts with some requirements but without
1b:Â OBG searches for PSU-ASPSP private key in FinTech vault using FinTech password. It is not found as id was empty.
1c: FinTech consent requirements are stored in PSU vault for further processing.
1d: FinTech is notified that PSU needs to authorize consent. FinTech redirects PSU to OBG.
2a: PSU provides the password to OBG login form that says some FinTech wants his consent
2b: PSUs PSU-ASPSP private key is read using the password supplied on the login.
2c: PSU-ASPSP private key is stored in FinTech vault INBOX
2d: FinTech consent requirements are read from PSU inbox using PSU password from login.
2e: Consent search module looks for matching consent using users' private key from private PSU vault storage

2i: Authorization secret key is generated. Consent requirements and matching consent details are encrypted with an authorization secret key and stored in the database in an encrypted form. Authorization secret key is converted to a cookie (1 to 1).
2j: User is asked for the agreement to share consent, consent details that are going to be shared are shown to the user for approval
2l: Consent is marked as shared to FinTech

2.1.b: Authorization secret key is generated. Consent requirements are encrypted with an authorization secret key and stored in the database in an encrypted form.
Authorization secret key is converted to a cookie (1 to 1).
2.1.c: User is sent to Consent configuration (consent embedded UI)
2.1.d: User lands on consent embedded UI, he possesses cookie with an encrypted key to read consent requirements
2.1.e: Bank protocol needs consent requirements to perform consent authorization
2.1.f: Consent requirements are read from the database and are decrypted using Authorization secret key decrypted from cookie
2.1.i: Consent is acquired based on its requirements
2.1.j: Consent is encrypted using users' public key
2.1.k: Encrypted consent is stored in the database. It can be read with by users' private key
2.1.l: User is shown page 'Back to FinTech' and navigates back to it

3a: Users lands back to FinTech, FinTech validates users' redirect cookie. FinTech has a PSU-ASPSP key id from redirection.
3b: FinTech calls consent confirmation endpoint

3c: Users' PSU-ASPSP key-id is being checked that it is shared with FinTech
3d: Users' PSU-ASPSP private key from inbox is moved into FinTech private space
3e: FinTech can now use PSU-ASPSP key-id
4a: FinTech calls list accounts with PSU-ASPSP key-id with password and requirements.
4b: PSU-ASPSP private key is read from FinTech private storage
4c: Consent search is done using PSU-ASPSP private key and consent requirements
4f: Consent is exchanged for account list at ASPSP
5a: Consent search in the database using private key
